2014: Made the cut in three of 10 LatinoamĂŠrica starts and had a pair of top-10 finishes. Best weeks were a T6 at the Lexus Panama Classic and a T9 at the Colombia Classic in Bogota. His second-round, 9-under 63 tied him for the best round of the tournament...Ended the season No. 53 on the Order of Merit...Tied for 39th at the News Sentinel Open. 2011: Missed the cut in the News Sentinel Open, his first career Web.com Tour start.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Two-time All-Sun Belt Conference selection in 2007-08. In 2007, he became the first player from Middle Tennessee State University to earn an at-large invitation to the NCAA Championship...Won a Tennessee State Junior title in 2004.
tourBios.personal: Attended Roane County High School in suburban Knoxville...Has one brother...Twitter account is @narramorechas...Says if he weren't playing golf for a living he'd be coaching the sport...Enjoys having a job that takes him outside every day...Enjoys spending time with his nephew...Favorite course he's played is Diamond Creek in Banner Elk, N.C., and would like to play Augusta National...Favorites include Duke basketball and the Denver Broncos, "NCIS" and "Top Gun." Enjoys the Candy Crush app...Likes to vacation in Las Vegas.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T28th at the Brasil Champions presented by Embrase.
